metadata.name: CR Art Sessions //2 #176
metadata.description:
Grayscale, Hold the Line, and Mondrian walk into a bar. The bartender looks up and says, "What is this, some kind of art project?"

Grayscale responds, "No, we're just here for a drink."

Hold the Line adds, "But we can definitely add some color to the place if you want."

Mondrian chimes in, "I prefer to keep things simple and stick to the basics."

The bartender shakes his head and says, "I'll be the judge of that. What can I get you all?"

Grayscale orders a Guinness, Hold the Line asks for a gin and tonic, and Mondrian asks for a glass of white wine.

The bartender serves up the drinks and says, "That will be $15.50, please."

Grayscale pulls out a twenty-dollar bill and hands it to the bartender, saying, "Keep the change."

The bartender thanks him and says, "Thanks, Grayscale. You always know how to liven up the place."

Hold the Line raises his glass and says, "Cheers to that!"

Mondrian nods and clinks glasses with the others, and the three of them enjoy their drinks and the rest of their evening at the bar.

-----

Press "e" to save a png (3240*4500 or 4500*3240 px) while in live mode.

-----

Artwork by @cristianrohr (2022)

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.name: Mandelroid #12
metadata.description:
The Mandelbrot set is a mathematical object that is generated by a simple formula, and it exhibits some interesting visual patterns that are reminiscent of those found in nature, such as the self-similarity of branching structures, the repetition of small-scale patterns on larger scales, and the presence of chaotic behavior.

The beauty of Polaroid film lies in its ability to capture and preserve a moment in space and time in a unique and tangible way.

This work combines two things that are incongruent with each other and brings them together to create a digital memory that serves as a reminder that complexity can be found even in the simplest things, that art is intrinsic to nature itself.

• press '1' to scale the photo to 1024x1024 pixels (the default output)
• press '2' to scale the photo to 2048x2048 pixels (Warning: can be slow!)
• press '3' to scale the photo to 4096x4096 pixels (Warning: can be very slow!)
• press 'd' to save the Mandelbrot Set
• press 's' to save the Polaroid film

Done with p5.js
Simone "OuterSilent" Ferrari | @outertales | December 2022

metadata.name: Henoheno Samurai #2164
metadata.description:
This work was inspired by Otsu-e(大津絵), a Japanese painting in the Edo period. Otsu-e were inexpensive paintings made as souvenirs. Although mass-produced using paper stencils, the artisans painted by hand, resulting in variations in the quality of their work. Connoisseurs found them interesting and collected them as works of art. Otsu-e showed a new value of beauty in Japanese art, different from Ukiyo-e (浮世絵) which are prints, and from fine art paintings which are one-of-a-kind artworks.

This work is made of canvas2D Bezier curves. Not just a combination of parts, but also a random displacement of the Bezier curve points to lose the shape. This is intended to create fun with the Otsu-e-like effect.


Features:
This profile is made up of 8 parts (brows, eyes, nose, mouth, ear, contour, hair, and body). Each part has 100 basic types. 
There are 7 skin colors and 12 kimono colors. Each RGB value of the colors is randomly added within a range of ±10. In addition, there are 70 kimono patterns. 
The distortion rate due to displacement of Bezier curve points is 0.0~50.0. 


BTW The title "Henoheno" is taken from the Japanese character picture "Henohenomoheji" known since the Edo period.

metadata.name: 凹凸 -ou_totsu- #14
metadata.description:
凹凸 -ou_totsu- Asahamiz

コンクリートブロック塀を眺めていました。
その時、壁の開口から夕日の日差しが差し込み、
自分のいる壁側には、また別の光線が影を生み出していました。

その二つの光線の行く末を想像の中で追っていました。
そんな散歩のひと時が、
約５か月間の自分のコーディングの時間に変わっていきました。

壁面には棒と穴を配置しました。
棒には私側の光線の影、
穴からは向こう側からの光線が差し込みます。

棒と穴の配置はrowcol,zigzag,curve の３パターンが入り交ざります。

各Featuresのパターンは色んな遊び要素を取り入れています。


"s","d","f"キーでpng保存が可能です。
"s"_screensize
"d"_2400px * 2400px
"f"_3600px * 3600px

是非お楽しみください。

Asahamiz

metadata.name: Harmonious Dissonance #18
metadata.description:
'Harmonious Dissonance' combines vertical lines, dots, and noise to evoke a unique visual experience. The canvas comes alive with a dynamic interplay of elements, creating an atmosphere that balances order and chaos.

Vertical lines stand as pillars of structure within the composition. They impart a sense of stability and direction, drawing the viewer's gaze upward and downward, guiding their exploration of the artwork's intricate details.

Amongst these lines are clusters of dots These dots vary in size and density, adding an element of randomness to the piece. From a distance, they create a harmonious texture, while up close, they reveal a fascinating world of individual nuances.

Flecks and fragments of color and texture emerge from the background. The position of lines are adjusted with noise. This noise disrupts the apparent order of the vertical lines and dots, injecting a hint of controlled chaos. 

'Harmonious Dissonance' melds the precision of vertical lines with the spontaneity of dots and the deliberate disorder of noise. It draws viewers into an ever-evolving dialogue between structure and spontaneity, cohesion and disruption.


Created with p5.js.
This was created as part of the GDAP 2023 Summer Class in Taipei.

metadata.name: Playground II #74
metadata.description:
"Playground II" is a Free abstract generative animated artwork. 
A giveaway/gift for the new year 2024!

Happy new year to all !!

CONTROLS
KEYS:

- 1-2: Set resolution from 1x to 2x of the current dimension (possibly slower performance in higher values)
- S: Save current screen in a 3x Resolution PNG
- A: Toggle Slideshow Mode (changes every 10 secs)
- Spacebar: Toggle Animation
- H: Toggle a Help Screen
- R: Reset - reload

MOUSE:

- Click: Generate new graphics

----
Made with p5js and custom shaders

© Jan. 2024  @Uniray_net | uniray.net

metadata.name: Timing #500
metadata.description:
Time.. 
While one thing happens one time, another happens several times.

----------------------------------------------------------------
  Keys control:
    r: toggle rotation
    i: increment rotation speed
    d: decrement rotation speed
    p: toggle show points
    s: save current size image to .png
    x + 2/4/8: save 2x/4x/8x size image to .png
    1-9 + g: save 1-9 sec animation to .gif (depends on the machine resources)

  URL parameters:
    fps=<value>: frame rate
    r=true: rotation ON
    p=false: do not show points

metadata.name: Automaton #40
metadata.description: An Elementary Cellular Automaton created with pure JavaScript. In this instance, the capability to invert the order of the rule has been added, and the drawing is performed from the bottom of the canvas to the top, resulting in a fresh perspective. Finally, a gradient is incorporated to accurately differentiate the states of the cells
